    "thinking": "The user is explaining a really important UX concept that I need to document. Let me break down what they're saying:\n\n1. **S3 - Image Management tab**: Consolidated upload area. When you're in \"upload mode\" gathering all images, you do it in ONE place, not jumping across 20 tabs.\n\n2. **Numbered tabs (like 13 - Zoning)**: Show \"Managed in Image Mgt\" link instead of upload box. This is where the image APPEARS in the report structure, but not where you upload it.\n\n3. **Split Panel Editor/Previewer**: This is the key insight:\n   - LEFT side: Editable fields (including image fields)\n   - RIGHT side: Live HTML preview of the actual report page\n   - The image shows IN CONTEXT next to the actual rendered page\n   - If you see \"oh shit my image looks bad\" you can fix it RIGHT THERE next to the preview\n   - You don't have to go back to S3 or wherever you originally uploaded it\n\n4. **The workflow**:\n   - TDD Dashboard (S3 tab) = Initial bulk upload mode\n   - Split Panel = Review/edit mode with live preview\n   - In the split panel, the image field IS editable right next to the page it appears on\n   - This is the \"best part\" - you see the rendered page and can edit the source field side-by-side\n\n5. **Future state**:\n   - TDD page might not even look like this\n   - Could be Google Drive folder upload that auto-populates\n   - The real work happens in the split panel editor where appraisers review and tweak\n\nThis is brilliant UX design - consolidate uploads in one place for initial setup, but allow inline editing in context when reviewing. I need to document this properly.",
